biography:

Aislyn is an independent researcher and developer who enjoys breathing life into research through code. Python came into Aislyn's life while studying acoustics in Finland: those long winter nights were just the right thing. She currently pulls from her academic background in clinical linguistic research and her life-long dance training to build smart applications processing sound and movement. She lives in Berlin and loves bike tours with her husband and daughter.
